The personal information controller of an organization must appoint a person or persons who shall be accountable for the organization’s compliance with the Act, and the identity of such person or persons must be disclosed to the data subjects upon the latter’s request. The Act does not specifically provide for the citizenship and residency of the data protection officer. The Act likewise does not specifically provide for penalties relating to the incorrect appointment of data protection officers.
For a specific step-by-step guideline on the registration of an entity’s DPO, please click here.Last modified 17 Dec 2021
				
			